# DataFlow json_schema: `additionalProperties` is MANDATORY

When using `json_schema` in `FormatStrPromptedGenerator`, `PromptedGenerator`, or
`operators.json` to constrain LLM structured output:

**Every `"type": "object"` in the schema MUST include `"additionalProperties": false`.**

Without it, OpenAI-compatible APIs return HTTP 500 and DataFlow retries infinitely.

## Python (`pipeline.py`)

```python
# ✅ CORRECT
json_schema={
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "score": {"type": "number"},
        "label": {"type": "string"},
    },
    "required": ["score", "label"],
    "additionalProperties": False,
}

# ❌ WRONG — causes API 500 infinite retry
json_schema={
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "score": {"type": "number"},
        "label": {"type": "string"},
    },
    "required": ["score", "label"],
}
```

## WebUI (`operators.json`)

```json
{"name": "json_schema", "value": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "score": {"type": "number"},
        "label": {"type": "string"}
    },
    "required": ["score", "label"],
    "additionalProperties": false
}}
```

## Nested objects — apply at EVERY level

```python
json_schema={
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "result": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {"value": {"type": "number"}},
            "required": ["value"],
            "additionalProperties": False,
        },
    },
    "required": ["result"],
    "additionalProperties": False,
}
```
